                <div class="col-md-9">
                    <img src="assets/img/clinical/clinical.png" class="img-fluid rounded mb-4" alt="Hero Image">
                    <br>
                    <h4 class="section-title">Clinical Study Summary</h4>
                    <p class="company">The company is currently engaged in numerous clinical studies that have</p>

                    <h4 class="section-title">Breakthrough Results</h4>
                    <p class="athletes">Achieved a 90% mycological cure rate—approximately 25% higher than reported in
                        leading published studies. Patients also experienced marked relief from perspiration and
                        pruritus (itchiness), demonstrating significant symptomatic improvement.


                    </p>
                    <h4 class="section-title">Recommended Usage</h4>
                    <p class="athletes">For best results, apply a thin layer of the product to the soles of your feet
                        and between the toes twice daily. We recommend showering at least once a day to remove any
                        excess product. To help prevent reinfection, change socks daily and regularly clean occlusive
                        footwear—such as sneakers and work boots—that may harbor fungus.
                    </p>
                    <h4 class="section-title">Patient Experience</h4>
                    <p class="athletes">Our trial participants love how easy our product is to use. Unlike traditional
                        athlete’s foot treatments that involve messy creams or powders, our convenient, easy-to-handle
                        stick glides smoothly over the foot and fits comfortably between the toes—making application
                        quick, clean, and hassle-free.
                    </p>
                    <h4 class="section-title">Clinical Claims</h4>
                    <p class="athletes">Most patients experienced improvements in bothersome Athlete’s Foot symptoms
                        within 2 weeks and most patients were cured at 4 weeks. Symptoms include sweaty feet, itchiness,
                        redness of skin.
                    </p>

